  "text": "Found gRPC service definitions shared between envoyproxy and grpc organizations. In sg-evals/data-plane-api--84e84367, the xDS API defines 8 gRPC service declarations: AggregatedDiscoveryService (ads.proto, StreamAggregatedResources/DeltaAggregatedResources RPCs), ClusterDiscoveryService (cds.proto), EndpointDiscoveryService (eds.proto), ListenerDiscoveryService (lds.proto), RouteDiscoveryService (rds.proto), SecretDiscoveryService (sds.proto), RuntimeDiscoveryService (rtds.proto), and HealthDiscoveryService (hds.proto, StreamHealthCheck/FetchHealthCheck RPCs). In sg-evals/grpc--957dba5e, the grpc_health_v1.Health service is defined in src/proto/grpc/health/v1/health.proto with Check (unary) and Watch (server-streaming) RPCs. The C++ implementation is in default_health_check_service.h/cc (DefaultHealthCheckService, HealthCheckServiceImpl) with the abstract interface in health_check_service_interface.h (HealthCheckServiceInterface). Python implementation is in grpc_health/v1/health.py (HealthServicer). The two orgs share gRPC as the transport protocol, and Envoy's HDS service (envoyproxy) is distinct from grpc_health_v1.Health (grpc org) — HDS manages health check assignments while Health reports individual service health status.",
